Qatar Foundation hosted Her Excellency Fatema Marouane, Morocco’s Minister of Handicrafts, Social Economy and Solidarity, on 25 December. A welcoming committee led by Engineer Saad Al Muhannadi, President of Qatar Foundation, received the Minister, at the Qatar Foundation Visitors Center.

HE Marouane is in Doha at the head of an official delegation from the Kingdom of Morocco, to foster greater commercial and industrial business cooperation between the State of Qatar and the Kingdom. The two nations however, are already linked through a number of agreements in various areas.

Appointed to her post earlier this year, HE Marouane is a member of Morocco’s National Council of the National Assembly of Independents and the Council of the Region of Casablanca City. She is also a laureate at the Faculty of Medicine of Lyon and former President of the Moroccan Endocrinology Diabetes and Nutrition Society (SMEDIAN).
